  "text": "The LV samples of 100 mg from eight animals in each group were used for the measurements of the amount of total protein and lipid hydroperoxide (LH) and for the enzyme determinations. Glutathione peroxidase (GSHPx, E.C.1.11.1.9), superoxide dismutase (SOD, E.C.1.15.1.1), and catalase (CAT, E.C.1.11.1.6) activity was assessed as previously specified [CITATION_1] . The cardiac energy metabolism was assessed with 3-hydroxyacyl coenzyme-A dehydrogenase (OHADH, E.C.1.1.1.35.) and lactate dehydrogenase (LDH, E.C.1.1.1.27) and citrate synthase (CS; E.C.4.1.3.7.) activities, as previously described [CITATION_2] . Enzyme activities were determined with a temperature-controlled microplate reader (Eon with Gen5 2.0 software connected to computer system control, BioTek Instruments, Winooski, VT, USA). All of the reagents were from Sigma (St. Louis, MO, USA).",
